messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/account/signup

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

HEAD acceptable:
- false

POST acceptable:
- true

OPTIONS acceptable:
- false

TRACE acceptable:
- false

GET acceptable:
- false

PUT acceptable:
- false

DELETE acceptable:
- false

PATCH acceptable:
- false

Explanation:
- The controller class has @RequestMapping("/api/account"), which sets the prefix for all endpoints in the class.
- The signup handler method is annotated with @PostMapping("/signup"), so the full path is the class prefix plus the method path: "/api/account/signup".
- @PostMapping explicitly registers the method for HTTP POST, so POST is true.
- There is no @RequestMapping, @GetMapping, @PutMapping, @DeleteMapping, @PatchMapping, @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.OPTIONS), nor any @RequestMapping for HEAD/TRACE on this path in the code provided. Following the instruction to base acceptability on the code (not runtime framework behavior), only POST is accepted; all other methods (including HEAD and OPTIONS) are reported as false.
- The "all HTTP methods acceptable" flag would override individual method results if true, but there is no code indicating that, so it is false.
